      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(directives): preserve think/verbose levels through inline directive clearing",
        "body": "When a message contains both real content and inline directives (e.g. webchat `/think` injection), `clearInlineDirectives` strips the directive syntax but also discards the parsed `thinkLevel` and `verboseLevel`. This causes the thinking effort to silently fall back to defaults for that run.\n\n**Fix:** Capture `thinkLevel` and `verboseLevel` before clearing, then re-inject them into the cleaned directives so they take effect for the run.\n\n**Files changed:** `src/auto-reply/reply/get-reply-directives.ts` (+14 lines)\n\nRelated: #38729 (enables xhigh for Anthropic — this PR ensures the level survives from input to execution)",
